Code coverage for pull requests:
Two good solutions:

codecov.io:
  https://codecov.io/
    "Pull Request Comments: featuring Coverage DiffsÂ®"
    "Coverage Compare: git diff with coverage overlay"
  https://codecov.io/docs
  Java Example: https://github.com/codecov/example-java
  There are browser extensions: see bottom of
    https://github.com/codecov/browser-extension/blob/master/readme.md
  http://vorba.ch/2015/java-gradle-travis-jacoco-codecov.html

Diff-cover is it!
https://github.com/Bachmann1234/diff-cover
"To check the coverage of your pull request, just go to the top level of the edx-platform codebase and run:"

Here are poor solutions.
Most tools give total code coverage, not for lines in the PR.
  Coveralls seems to give total code coverage, not for lines in the PR.
    https://coveralls.io/features
    Same for most other services.
  Shippable: like Coveralls?
    https://github.com/Shippable/support/issues/239
  Shamer: global, not per-PR; has a leaderboard
  Code Climate -- not for Java?

===========================================================================

For a new person to take advantage of a project that already has Codecov integration:

Sign up for Codecov (this is necessary once on each computer+browser
combination you use):
https://codecov.io/login/github

Install a browser extension: see the bottom of
    https://github.com/codecov/browser-extension/blob/master/readme.md

Browse to a URL such as
https://github.com/randoop/randoop/blob/master/src/main/java/randoop/JavaFileWriter.java
and you should see the covered lines in green and the uncovered lines in red.

===========================================================================

Sign up for Codecov:
https://codecov.io/login/github

The rest of this is for Maven integration.
For Gradle integration instead:
http://vorba.ch/2015/java-gradle-travis-jacoco-codecov.html

Fork
https://github.com/codecov/example-java
to create
https://github.com/mernst/example-java

cd ~/java
git clone git@github.com:mernst/example-java.git

At
https://travis-ci.org/profile/mernst
click on
"sync account"
and then in the list enable
mernst/example-java

Browse to
https://github.com/mernst/example-java
and see "build unknown" next to the repository slug.

trigger-travis.sh mernst example-java `cat ~/private/.travis-access-token` "Initial build"

Wait 10 or more seconds to see a build running at
https://travis-ci.org/mernst/example-java

Problem:  I see "no coverage" at
https://github.com/mernst/example-java/blob/master/src/main/java/org/jacoco/examples/maven/java/HelloWorld.java
That's because there is no
  script: mvn test
line in .travis.yml!
When I run "mvn test, I see output at
  ~/java/example-java/target/site/jacoco:

